'They are based on some houses excavated at the nearby henge of Durrington Walls,’ Susan Greaney, an archaeologist and the museum’s curator, says. 'They date from 2500bc, the same time as the large sarsen stones were being raised at Stonehenge and probably where the builders of Stonehenge lived. It will be a real hands-on, immersive experience. We hope the exhibition will show that the prehistoric people who built and used Stonehenge were sophisticated and clever.
